title: First Nations Ambassador racks up $350k travel bill
description: Sky News contributor Jaimee Rogers analyses reports Labor’s First Nations Ambassador Justin Mohamed racking up an eyewatering $350,000 travel bill.

title: Majority of Brits in favour of under 16s social media ban
description: Former Liberal MP Nicolle Flint analyses how most Britons are in favour of an under 16s social media ban in the UK.

title: ‘Snivelling coward’: Former speaker of the House slams Albanese’s royal commission debacle
description: Former speaker of the House Bronwyn Bishop speaks on the families of the Bondi terror attack victims demanding a royal commission from the Albanese government.

title: Aussies face $2,000 extra in bills as cost of living crisis worsens
description: Sky News contributor Jaimee Rogers analyses how Australian households will likely face a combined bill for energy, insurance, food and housing which will total around $2,000.

title: Trump claims Ukraine war will end soon in Zelensky meeting
description: Former Labor MP Michael Danby unpacks United States President Donald Trump claiming the war in Ukraine will end soon.

title: ‘Everyone’s talking about it’: Bondi families pen open letter for royal commission to Albanese
description: Writer and broadcaster Kel Richards analyses the “deafening” calls for a Commonwealth royal commission into the Bondi terror attack.

title: ‘Beautiful book’: Tony Abbott lauded for ‘Australia: A History’
description: Writer and broadcaster Kel Richards highlights the “gripping” book written by former prime minister Tony Abbott entitled ‘Australia: A History’.

title: Labor ‘quietly’ increases diversity and gender targets for lawyers
description: Writer and broadcaster Kel Richards highlights how the Albanese government has quietly increased gender targets and expanded diversity measures for lawyers.

title: ‘Help save someone else’: Coward’s punch attack leads to national awareness campaign
description: ‘Stop, One Punch Can Kill’ Co-Founder Caterina Politi joins writer and broadcaster Kel Richards to highlight the dangers of the ‘coward’s punch’ 13 years on from her son’s death.

title: ‘Debunked the hype’: Power prices up 40 per cent under Labor’s renewables agenda
description: Writer and broadcaster Kel Richards analyses the Liberal Party abandoning net zero as power prices are up 40 per cent since Labor implemented the renewables agenda.

title: ‘Somehow I woke up’: Explorer recounts horror climb after fall into precipice at 8,300 metres
description: Writer and broadcaster Kel Richards sits down with Sky News contributor Adrian Hayes as Mr Hayes recounts his perilous experience climbing Mount Kanchenjunga.

title: NSW considers sending troops to protect Sydney’s Jewish community during events
description: Sky News host Freya Leach analyses New South Wales Premier Chris Minns considering Army troops for Jewish safety at events in the state.

title: Australians embracing a cashless future is leaving millions behind
description: Sky News contributor Joe Hildebrand analyses how a cashless shift in society is leaving those who prefer the older payment method behind.

title: US town complains about smell from local doughnut factory
description: Sky News contributor Joe Hildebrand highlights how a small town in the US is complaining about the smell of doughnuts from a local factory.

title: Kremlin claims peace with Ukraine is ‘a lot closer’
description: The Kremlin has supported United States President Donald Trump's assertion a peace deal between Russia and Ukraine is closer.
